[[unpartei/HumanoidAgents|HumanoidAgents]][[http://google.com/search?q=HumanoidAgents|➜°]] could fake democracy in the future
//a stance for radical transparency ..//

Supposed it is true, that there are only a couple of people with incredibly much money, who want to rule the world.
Supposed you are one of them. What would you do?

A: I would motivate (even urge) the people to write under a pseudonym and taking an artificial avatar instead of their real personal portrait.
Q: Why that?
A: Because this way, the social networks could be populated by millions of [[unpartei/BotAvatars|BotAvatars]][[http://google.com/search?q=BotAvatars|➜°]]➜°, who create a public opinion and even a political will.
Q: Do you mean it might technically be feasable to give each natural person the illusion, that there are much more persons, who wish to realize different goals than you and your buddies?
A: Yes. I guess so.
Q: Can you give me a hint?
A: Imagine that it becomes possible to create super-photo-realistic avatars, who can express emotions in a typical human way, transporting their messages, discussions and even group consensus to influence the smaller rest of human actors that are acting online.
A: Do you have a link for such possible artificial agents?
Q: Not directly .. but take the following one for thinking about it:

http://www.chrisshorts.com/haptekHeads1.html

